Ismail Momoniat has been appointed acting director general at the National Treasury (eNCA/Screenshot) JOHANNESBURG - Ismail Momoniat has been appointed acting director-general of the National Treasury. Momoniat's appointment follows the departure of Dondo Mogajane, who held the position for five years. Momoniat has worked in Treasury for 27-years and has previously served as the Deputy Director-General. READ:Â Dondo Mogajane leaves Treasury He was instrumental in driving financial and fiscal legislation to give effect to the 1996 Constitution. Finance Minister Enoch Godongwana says he is confident Momoniat will provide a steady hand and ensure continuity. Ismail Momoniat has been appointed acting director-general of the National Treasury. Momoniat's appointment follows the departure of Dondo Mogajane, who held the position for five years. Momoniat has worked in Treasury for 27-years. #DStv403 #eNCA pic.twitter.com/iVs3OjDdO0